      passage: `<p>Domesticated thousands of years ago in South America, the tomato deviates structurally from the wild plant it is descended from. Maize (corn), another domesticated crop from the Americas, doesn’t closely resemble any wild plant, and genetic research only recently ______ its ancestor to be teosinte grass.</p>`,
